\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Average DEA efficiency scores for Greek occupational pension funds (2017--2020). The efficiency frontier (score = 1.0) represents best-practice performance. Source: Chrysanthopoulou, Mavrommati and Migdalas (2023).}}{17}{figure.caption.3}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Distribution of CRS technical efficiency scores for Greek occupational pension funds, 2017--2020. Source: Chrysanthopoulou, Mavrommati and Migdalas (2023).}}{18}{figure.caption.4}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Estimated composition of the Zimbabwean pension fund sector by fund type (IPEC, 2023). Self-administered and insured funds collectively account for approximately 63\% of the sector.}}{19}{figure.caption.5}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Input--output framework for DEA efficiency measurement of Zimbabwean pension funds. Each pension fund constitutes a Decision-Making Unit (DMU) evaluated against the best-practice efficiency frontier.}}{20}{figure.caption.6}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Five-stage DEA modelling framework applied to Zimbabwean pension fund efficiency analysis. Adapted from Chrysanthopoulou, Mavrommati and Migdalas (2023).}}{28}{figure.caption.8}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Seven-stage hybrid DEA--machine learning framework. The five-stage DEA core is extended by Simar--Wilson bootstrap bias correction (Stage 6) and Random Forest determinant analysis (Stage 7), addressing the deterministic and finite-sample limitations of standard DEA.}}{31}{figure.caption.9}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Distribution of CRS technical efficiency scores for Zimbabwean pension funds by year, 2021--2025. The proportion of fully efficient funds (33.3\%) remained constant, while efficiency among the remaining funds deteriorated in 2023 before recovering in 2024--2025.}}{37}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces CRS and VRS average technical efficiency scores for the twelve Zimbabwean pension fund DMUs, 2021--2025. Four funds achieve full efficiency under both model specifications.}}{39}{figure.caption.17}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Random Forest variable importance rankings (MDI scores) for six candidate determinants of Zimbabwean self-administered pension fund efficiency. Exchange rate volatility and annual inflation rate are identified as the dominant macroeconomic constraints on efficiency, collectively accounting for approximately 56\% of total variable importance.}}{44}{figure.caption.22}%
